# StudyForge Environment Configuration

As StudyForge is a local-first application, environment variables are only meant for local proxy configuration, feature flags, or compile-time defaults.

# Note on BYOK (Bring Your Own Key) Security
All external provider keys (such as OpenAI or Google Gemini API keys) are **NOT** stored inside environment variables. 
Instead, StudyForge uses an AES-256 encrypted local vault within IndexedDB, shielded by a Master Password. Keys are injected directly from memory upon client request to proxy servers rather than being bundled in build files.

To run custom proxy endpoints or adjust platform settings safely:

```env
# Optional feature flag
VITE_ENABLE_DEBUG_TOOLS=false
VITE_LOG_LEVEL=info
```
